definitions.definition: A cut of meat, often containing a section of a rib .
examples: I only like lamb chops with mint jelly.

definitions.definition: A blow with an axe , cleaver , or similar implement .
examples: It should take just one good chop to fell the sapling.

definitions.definition: ( martial arts ) A blow delivered with the hand rigid and outstretched.
Ocean waves , generally caused by wind , distinguished from swell by being smaller and not lasting as long.
( poker ) A hand where two or more players have an equal-valued hand, resulting in the chips being shared equally between them.
examples: With both players having an ace-high straight, the pot was a chop .

definitions.definition: ( informal , with "the" ) Termination, especially from employment; the sack .
( Australia , New Zealand ) A woodchopping competition.
( dated ) A crack or cleft ; a chap .
( uncountable ) Aircraft turbulence .
( UK , slang ) Cocaine .
( MLE , slang ) A knife , especially one used as a weapon.

definitions.definition: ( chiefly in the plural ) A jaw of an animal .
A movable jaw or cheek , as of a vice .
The land at each side of the mouth of a river , harbour , or channel .

definitions.definition: ( colloquial , India , Hong Kong , Malaysia , Singapore , Brunei ) A stamp or seal ; a mark , imprint or impression on a document (or other object or material) made by stamping or sealing a design with ink or wax, respectively, or by other methods. [from 19th c.]
( colloquial , by extension , Malaysia , Singapore , Brunei ) The device used for stamping or sealing, which also contains the design to be imprinted.
A mark indicating nature , quality , or brand .
A licence or passport that has been sealed.
A complete shipment .
